$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(28, 36, '<p>High School Teaching Positions for the 2016-17 School Year<br />\\r\\n&nbsp;<br />\\r\\nBaxter Academy for Technology and Science is hiring teachers for its 2016-17 school year. &nbsp;We are a public charter school in downtown Portland, Maine, that opened September 2013. Currently we have over 300 students in grades 9-12 and are graduating our first senior class. &nbsp;We have a commitment to providing access to STEM education and are a project-based learning environment led by student inquiry and focused on a cross-disciplinary approach. &nbsp;You can find more information on our school and current faculty at our website: <a href=\\\"http://www.baxter-academy.org\\\">www.baxter-academy.org</a>. &nbsp;<br />\\r\\n&nbsp;<br />\\r\\nTeachers applying to join us will have demonstrated excellence in teaching and scholarship in her or his field. &nbsp;To apply, please <a href=\\\"documents/BaxterTeacherApplication.pdf\\\">complete the online application</a> and send a resume or CV with references to</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<blockquote>\\r\\n<p>Michele LaForge, Head of School, Baxter Academy for Technology and Science,</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>54 York Street,</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Portland, Maine, 04101. &nbsp;</p>\\r\\n</blockquote>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Additional material that highlights teaching, such as a philosophy statement; recommendations from students, parents, or colleagues; or anything that illustrates your passion for education, is highly encouraged. &nbsp;Interviews will begin three weeks from the date of this posting, and only final candidates will be contacted. &nbsp;<br />\\r\\n&nbsp;<br />\\r\\n<strong>Life Science Teacher (1.0 FTE)</strong> - Baxter seeks an innovative, creative, and adaptive science teacher with interest and experience in inquiry-based, problem-focused, and student-centered Science instruction. Immediate needs include biology (anatomy &amp; physiology, biochemistry, genetics, and microbiology), along with chemistry. With the other Faculty, the candidate will be expected to develop relevant, interesting, and innovative curriculum. Dual training or endorsement (Life Science and Physical Science) and eligibility for Maine certification preferred. Flexibility with varying roles and assignments, plus an ability and eagerness to collaborate with other teachers (both inside and outside of the classroom) will be essential to success.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Mathematics Teacher (1.0 FTE)</strong> - Baxter seeks an innovative, creative, and adaptive math teacher with interest and experience in inquiry-based, problem-focused and student-centered Mathematics instruction. A proven ability to teach a variety of concepts and skills ranging from Numeracy through Statistics and Calculus is preferred. Flexibility with varying roles and assignments, plus an ability and eagerness to collaborate with other teachers, will be essential to success.<br />\\r\\n&nbsp;<br />\\r\\n<strong>Humanities Teachers (2.0 FTE)</strong> - Baxter seeks innovative and dynamic humanities teachers who are comfortable collaborating across disciplines. The position requires creative, project-based teaching that fosters student-driven inquiry. &nbsp;Dual training or certification (English and Social Studies) preferred.<br />\\r\\n&nbsp;<br />\\r\\n<strong>Ed Tech III - (1.0 FTE)</strong> - Will support special ed teachers and coordinator with preparation of classroom materials and class management functions; supervise small groups of students in project-based programs; conduct one-on-one or small groups with indirect professional supervision; provide input to completion and maintenance of individual observational child assessment; introduce new learning, pre-planned in collaboration with the special education teacher and coordinator; any other appropriate duties the Site/Director/Supervisor deems necessary involving students with IEPs.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Our needs are subject to change and we welcome applications from people passionate and committed to STEM education whose experience may not fit neatly into positions listed above.</p>\\r\\n', 'High School Teaching Positions for the 2016-17 School Year   Baxter Academy for Technology and Science is hiring teachers for its 2016-17 school year.  We are a public charter school in downtown Portland, Maine, that opened September 2013. Currently we have over 300 students in grades 9-12 and are graduating our first senior class.  We have a commitment to providing access to STEM education and are a project-based learning environment led by student inquiry and focused on a cross-disciplinary approach.  You can find more information on our school and current faculty at our website: www.baxter-academy.org.     Teachers applying to join us will have demonstrated excellence in teaching and scholarship in her or his field.  To apply, please complete the online application and send a resume or CV with references to Michele LaForge, Head of School, Baxter Academy for Technology and Science, 54 York Street, Portland, Maine, 04101.   Additional material that highlights teaching, such as a philosophy statement; recommendations from students, parents, or colleagues; or anything that illustrates your passion for education, is highly encouraged.  Interviews will begin three weeks from the date of this posting, and only final candidates will be contacted.     Life Science Teacher (1.0 FTE) - Baxter seeks an innovative, creative, and adaptive science teacher with interest and experience in inquiry-based, problem-focused, and student-centered Science instruction. Immediate needs include biology (anatomy &amp; physiology, biochemistry, genetics, and microbiology), along with chemistry. With the other Faculty, the candidate will be expected to develop relevant, interesting, and innovative curriculum. Dual training or endorsement (Life Science and Physical Science) and eligibility for Maine certification preferred. Flexibility with varying roles and assignments, plus an ability and eagerness to collaborate with other teachers (both inside and outside of the classroom) will be essential to success. Mathematics Teacher (1.0 FTE) - Baxter seeks an innovative, creative, and adaptive math teacher with interest and experience in inquiry-based, problem-focused and student-centered Mathematics instruction. A proven ability to teach a variety of concepts and skills ranging from Numeracy through Statistics and Calculus is preferred. Flexibility with varying roles and assignments, plus an ability and eagerness to collaborate with other teachers, will be essential to success.   Humanities Teachers (2.0 FTE) - Baxter seeks innovative and dynamic humanities teachers who are comfortable collaborating across disciplines. The position requires creative, project-based teaching that fosters student-driven inquiry.  Dual training or certification (English and Social Studies) preferred.   Ed Tech III - (1.0 FTE) - Will support special ed teachers and coordinator with preparation of classroom materials and class management functions; supervise small groups of students in project-based programs; conduct one-on-one or small groups with indirect professional supervision; provide input to completion and maintenance of individual observational child assessment; introduce new learning, pre-planned in collaboration with the special education teacher and coordinator; any other appropriate duties the Site/Director/Supervisor deems necessary involving students with IEPs. Our needs are subject to change and we welcome applications from people passionate and committed to STEM education whose experience may not fit neatly into positions listed above.');";
$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(30, 38, '<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><u>Admissions &amp; Enrollment Forms</u></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\">\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<p><a href=\\\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1fn3jMu5O6ox8gRhlhEHP2vKVcgkIBn9G_VSkSmS_y1o/viewform?c=0&w=1\\\">Baxter Academy Admissions Application 2016 - 2017 School Year</a></p>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<p><a href=\\\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1Q8gXhGEq964AATW-fQZbiqwumzfEqy-A7tqOPvTFhXk/viewform?c=0&w=1\\\">Baxter Open Day</a>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<p><a href=\\\"http://static1.squarespace.com/static/51e4a401e4b0ead5a3b591b5/t/565df24de4b03071352b6627/1448997453444/letter+of+intent+to+enroll+2016-2017.pdf\\\">Letter of Intent to Enroll</a></p>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<p><a href=\\\"http://static1.squarespace.com/static/51e4a401e4b0ead5a3b591b5/t/565dadf9e4b011b0652872f0/1448979961881/Commitment+to+Enroll+2016-2017+%281%29.pdf\\\">Commitment to Enroll</a></p>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><br />\\r\\n<u>Forms for Current Baxter Families</u></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\">\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<p><a href=\\\"http://Medication Authorization Form Release and Waiver of Liability\\\">Medication Authorization Form Release and Waiver of Liability</a></p>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<p><a href=\\\"http://static1.squarespace.com/static/51e4a401e4b0ead5a3b591b5/t/530cb432e4b07902c6478f61/1393341490640/OpenCampusContract2013-14+%283%29.pdf\\\">Acknowledgement Form for Baxter Academy Open Campus</a></p>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<p><a href=\\\"http://static1.squarespace.com/static/51e4a401e4b0ead5a3b591b5/t/5283de94e4b0a6f04e676b01/1384373908625/Copy_of_FamilyOrderFormBrand+FamilyOrderFormBrand.pdf\\\">Family Gift Card Order Forms</a></p>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n	<li>\\r\\n	<p><a href=\\\"http://static1.squarespace.com/static/51e4a401e4b0ead5a3b591b5/t/55f1ba5ae4b0f5a6cc392161/1441905242693/Laptop+use+form2015-2016.pdf\\\">Laptop Usage Form</a></p>\\r\\n	</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><br />\\r\\n<u>Forms for Current Baxter Students</u></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https://docs.google.com/a/baxter-academy.org/forms/d/1Zsbv9kRbJj1SGy1ekLSsH1XwQw8pXu6ZEE2YFY8T4CY/viewform\\\">Baxter Fundraising</a></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\">Maine Work Permit: <a href=\\\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TZNk2g3GPUkRk1iTDd7--GskiOzsuGXHtBuD5WS81d0/edit?ts=57327235\\\">Info</a> | <a href=\\\"maine_work_permit.pdf\\\">Form</a></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><br />\\r\\n<u><span style=\\\"line-height: 1.6em;\\\">Policies</span></u><span style=\\\"line-height: 1.6em;\\\">&nbsp;</span></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><a href=\\\"http://static1.squarespace.com/static/51e4a401e4b0ead5a3b591b5/t/55ccfa65e4b0dc6eee3e3c46/1439496805553/Baxter+Policy+%282%29.pdf\\\">BAXTER ACADEMY NONDISCRIMINATION/EQUAL OPPORTUNITY AND AFFIRMATIVE ACTION</a></p>\\r\\n', 'Admissions &amp; Enrollment Forms Baxter Academy Admissions Application 2016 - 2017 School Year Baxter Open Day  Letter of Intent to Enroll Commitment to Enroll Forms for Current Baxter Families Medication Authorization Form Release and Waiver of Liability Acknowledgement Form for Baxter Academy Open Campus Family Gift Card Order Forms Laptop Usage Form Forms for Current Baxter Students Baxter Fundraising Maine Work Permit: Info | Form Policies  BAXTER ACADEMY NONDISCRIMINATION/EQUAL OPPORTUNITY AND AFFIRMATIVE ACTION');";
$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(30, 39, '<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><strong>What is Baxter Academy?</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\">Baxter Academy is a public charter school in Portland, Maine. Its curriculum is rooted in inquiry and project-based learning and is connected across subjects. Baxter opened in fall 2013 with a learning community of 130 freshman and sophomore students from more than 20 Maine towns. Its teacher to student ratio is 1:16. It is free to attend Baxter Academy.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><strong>Where is Baxter Academy?</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\">Baxter Academy is located in downtown Portland at 54 York Street.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><strong>Who is Baxter Academy?</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\">Who are the students who thrive at Baxter? Baxter students are innovative and ethical. They are curious and motivated. They are willing to take risks, to fail, and to reflect in order to learn. They are inclusive of others. They take personal responsibility but are geared towards collaboration. They are musicians and photographers, martial artists and dancers, quarterbacks and video gamers. They love reading. Or taking apart cars and putting them back together. They collect LPs or books or trains. They may dream of being a doctor, a video game developer, a sustainability expert, a craftsman, an engineer, a designer, a climatologist, a cancer researcher, a wildlife photographer, or a ____________.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><strong>What&rsquo;s the faculty like?</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\">Baxter faculty are innovative and ethical. They are curious and motivated. They are willing to take risks, to fail, and to reflect in order to learn. They are inclusive of others. They take personal responsibility but are geared towards collaboration. As a group, they have taught all over the United States and Ukraine and China. Together, they speak many languages and play many musical instruments. Some are from Maine. Some are from away. One has built robots on US military contracts and another has built kayaks from cedar strips. One has a degree in particle physics but also experiments with photographic techniques from the Civil War. One teaches chemistry and writes murder mysteries. Every one of them is attentive, responsive, and caring. And they are still learning. Every day.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><strong>What about the administration?</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\">Baxter&rsquo;s administrative staff are innovative and ethical. They are curious and motivated... You see where we&rsquo;re going with this: We think it&rsquo;s important that the adults in the school share the same wonderful traits as the students. The school&rsquo;s executive director, Carl Stasio, brings wisdom and nearly three decades of leadership experience in Maine education. Head of School Michele LaForge brims over with creativity in designing the school around its unique mission&mdash;and she is nurturing and tough-minded, too.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><strong>What&rsquo;s different about Baxter Academy?</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\">Baxter Academy offers a well-rounded education with an emphasis on deeply engaging students in hands-on study of science, technology, engineering, and math. Baxter has a robust and lively humanities department, as well as Mandarin language taught by a native speaker. Electives in 2013-14 have included music ensemble, photography, CAD, JAVA, furniture building, creative writing, journalism, and graphic design. Students engage in projects of their own choosing, as well as school-wide explorations that knit together the disciplines. On Fridays, the students work on FLEX FRIDAY group projects of their design and implementation. Each project has a faculty advisor. This year, some of those include an underwater robot, a canoe, a mural, a radio station, high-speed photography, video games, a green roof for the school, and mobility footgear for a virtual-reality platform. Inquiry leads the learning at Baxter. Students think for themselves. They analyze. They innovate. Busy work doesn&rsquo;t happen here, but everyone is always busy with meaningful, exciting work.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><strong>Can my child attend Baxter Academy?</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\">If your child is a Maine resident rising into the ninth tenth, or eleventh grade, he or she is eligible to enroll at Baxter.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><strong>How do I enroll my student?</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\">Fill out the online application, found on our Home Page, and send in a hard-copy Letter of Intent to Enroll to add your student&#39;s name to the waitlist. Follow the Admissions updates online at http://baxter-academy.org/admissions/. We host Open Houses in the Fall and Winter. The Open Enrollment period begins in December or January, ending with a Lottery held in February or March.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><b>I have a question that&#39;s not on this list?</b></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\">Please feel free to visit our <a href=\\\"contactus\\\">contact page</a>!</p>\\r\\n', 'What is Baxter Academy? Baxter Academy is a public charter school in Portland, Maine. Its curriculum is rooted in inquiry and project-based learning and is connected across subjects. Baxter opened in fall 2013 with a learning community of 130 freshman and sophomore students from more than 20 Maine towns. Its teacher to student ratio is 1:16. It is free to attend Baxter Academy. Where is Baxter Academy? Baxter Academy is located in downtown Portland at 54 York Street. Who is Baxter Academy? Who are the students who thrive at Baxter? Baxter students are innovative and ethical. They are curious and motivated. They are willing to take risks, to fail, and to reflect in order to learn. They are inclusive of others. They take personal responsibility but are geared towards collaboration. They are musicians and photographers, martial artists and dancers, quarterbacks and video gamers. They love reading. Or taking apart cars and putting them back together. They collect LPs or books or trains. They may dream of being a doctor, a video game developer, a sustainability expert, a craftsman, an engineer, a designer, a climatologist, a cancer researcher, a wildlife photographer, or a ____________. What’s the faculty like? Baxter faculty are innovative and ethical. They are curious and motivated. They are willing to take risks, to fail, and to reflect in order to learn. They are inclusive of others. They take personal responsibility but are geared towards collaboration. As a group, they have taught all over the United States and Ukraine and China. Together, they speak many languages and play many musical instruments. Some are from Maine. Some are from away. One has built robots on US military contracts and another has built kayaks from cedar strips. One has a degree in particle physics but also experiments with photographic techniques from the Civil War. One teaches chemistry and writes murder mysteries. Every one of them is attentive, responsive, and caring. And they are still learning. Every day. What about the administration? Baxter’s administrative staff are innovative and ethical. They are curious and motivated... You see where we’re going with this: We think it’s important that the adults in the school share the same wonderful traits as the students. The school’s executive director, Carl Stasio, brings wisdom and nearly three decades of leadership experience in Maine education. Head of School Michele LaForge brims over with creativity in designing the school around its unique mission—and she is nurturing and tough-minded, too. What’s different about Baxter Academy? Baxter Academy offers a well-rounded education with an emphasis on deeply engaging students in hands-on study of science, technology, engineering, and math. Baxter has a robust and lively humanities department, as well as Mandarin language taught by a native speaker. Electives in 2013-14 have included music ensemble, photography, CAD, JAVA, furniture building, creative writing, journalism, and graphic design. Students engage in projects of their own choosing, as well as school-wide explorations that knit together the disciplines. On Fridays, the students work on FLEX FRIDAY group projects of their design and implementation. Each project has a faculty advisor. This year, some of those include an underwater robot, a canoe, a mural, a radio station, high-speed photography, video games, a green roof for the school, and mobility footgear for a virtual-reality platform. Inquiry leads the learning at Baxter. Students think for themselves. They analyze. They innovate. Busy work doesn’t happen here, but everyone is always busy with meaningful, exciting work. Can my child attend Baxter Academy? If your child is a Maine resident rising into the ninth tenth, or eleventh grade, he or she is eligible to enroll at Baxter. How do I enroll my student? Fill out the online application, found on our Home Page, and send in a hard-copy Letter of Intent to Enroll to add your student&#039;s name to the waitlist. Follow the Admissions updates online at http://baxter-academy.org/admissions/. We host Open Houses in the Fall and Winter. The Open Enrollment period begins in December or January, ending with a Lottery held in February or March. I have a question that&#039;s not on this list? Please feel free to visit our contact page!');";
$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(31, 43, '<p style=\\\"margin-left: 40px;\\\">At Baxter Academy, we believe students learn what matters most by being integrated directly into the work of the world. We collaborate with a robust network of responsive real-world partners who provide mentorship, internships, and opportunities for students to work within&mdash;and solve problems for&mdash;our community.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-left: 40px;\\\">If you do work in Maine&mdash;whether in a STEM field, or social services, or creative arts&mdash;Baxter wants to connect you with our students. We think you&rsquo;ll soon witness the value of having young minds become acquainted with the most urgent problems you face and with your search for solutions.</p>\\r\\n', 'At Baxter Academy, we believe students learn what matters most by being integrated directly into the work of the world. We collaborate with a robust network of responsive real-world partners who provide mentorship, internships, and opportunities for students to work within—and solve problems for—our community. If you do work in Maine—whether in a STEM field, or social services, or creative arts—Baxter wants to connect you with our students. We think you’ll soon witness the value of having young minds become acquainted with the most urgent problems you face and with your search for solutions.');";
$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(31, 44, '<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><span style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\">&bull;&nbsp;</span><strong style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\">Be a mentor.</strong><span style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\">&nbsp;Share your expertise with students interested in learning more about the work you do&mdash;and what it takes to do it well. Your time is important to us, so you&rsquo;ll give in a way that meets your needs.</span></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\">&bull;&nbsp;<strong>Our internship program</strong>&nbsp;has been designed around students creating &ldquo;deliverables&rdquo; requested by partnering organizations. Students apply internally for the internships and must provide evidence to a faculty committee that they have the necessary skills and background to successfully meet the &ldquo;client&rsquo;s&rdquo; needs.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\"><em>Examples of current internships include student teams making short documentaries for research institutes and hospitals; redesigning websites to integrate form and function; and working alongside scientists in labs.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\">&bull;&nbsp;<strong>Flex Friday flagship projects</strong>&nbsp;use interlocking teams of students to extend research and development for and with industry/research partners.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px; margin-left: 40px;\\\"><em>We have teams of students working with industry leaders to improve student work while acquainting students with the real-world concerns of professionals in the field. Students use their CAD-skills to create prototypes. They crunch data. They do field research.</em></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\">Industry leaders have recognized how these real-world efforts accelerate the development of innovative thinkers with important cutting-edge skills. While visiting Baxter, the founder of Boston Dynamics said,<em>&nbsp;&ldquo;The key skills we look for in job applicants at Boston Dynamics are the ones we see being developed by students at Baxter Academy&mdash;and those skills are sometimes hard to find even among strong college graduates.&rdquo;</em>&nbsp;At Baxter, we believe that real-world partnerships accelerate and amplify the learning that matters most.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 20.8px;\\\"><strong>Do you have a problem Baxter students can help solve?</strong>&nbsp;Tap it into our matching system here, and we&rsquo;ll get back to you soon to see how Baxter students can best serve your needs.</p>\\r\\n', '• Be a mentor. Share your expertise with students interested in learning more about the work you do—and what it takes to do it well. Your time is important to us, so you’ll give in a way that meets your needs. • Our internship program has been designed around students creating “deliverables” requested by partnering organizations. Students apply internally for the internships and must provide evidence to a faculty committee that they have the necessary skills and background to successfully meet the “client’s” needs. Examples of current internships include student teams making short documentaries for research institutes and hospitals; redesigning websites to integrate form and function; and working alongside scientists in labs. • Flex Friday flagship projects use interlocking teams of students to extend research and development for and with industry/research partners. We have teams of students working with industry leaders to improve student work while acquainting students with the real-world concerns of professionals in the field. Students use their CAD-skills to create prototypes. They crunch data. They do field research. Industry leaders have recognized how these real-world efforts accelerate the development of innovative thinkers with important cutting-edge skills. While visiting Baxter, the founder of Boston Dynamics said, “The key skills we look for in job applicants at Boston Dynamics are the ones we see being developed by students at Baxter Academy—and those skills are sometimes hard to find even among strong college graduates.” At Baxter, we believe that real-world partnerships accelerate and amplify the learning that matters most. Do you have a problem Baxter students can help solve? Tap it into our matching system here, and we’ll get back to you soon to see how Baxter students can best serve your needs.');";
$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(33, 50, '<h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Flex Friday dedicates 20 percent of the week to student-managed, long-term projects that are relevant to each student&rsquo;s interests and goals. &nbsp;Student teams identify a real-world problem, define how they might solve it, pitch their solution to a faculty review board, network with outside experts, and then set to work.<br />\\r\\n</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Some students may choose to work in a large group to develop an experimental model for a fish hatchery, others may want to work individually on a writing a database program with a local company.</h3>\\r\\n', '     Flex Friday dedicates 20 percent of the week to student-managed, long-term projects that are relevant to each student’s interests and goals.  Student teams identify a real-world problem, define how they might solve it, pitch their solution to a faculty review board, network with outside experts, and then set to work.      Some students may choose to work in a large group to develop an experimental model for a fish hatchery, others may want to work individually on a writing a database program with a local company.');";
$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(33, 51, '<h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Groups of students are able to coalesce around projects of common interest and work collaboratively without scheduling difficulties.</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Teachers, freed from other teaching obligations, are able to focus on advising students as they work through their projects, assisting with skill development and making sure they ask the right questions, follow through on their work plans and collaborate effectively within work groups.</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n', '     Groups of students are able to coalesce around projects of common interest and work collaboratively without scheduling difficulties.      Teachers, freed from other teaching obligations, are able to focus on advising students as they work through their projects, assisting with skill development and making sure they ask the right questions, follow through on their work plans and collaborate effectively within work groups.  ');";
$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(33, 52, '<h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Flex Friday fosters the skills needed to succeed in the real world; these skills require time, responsibility, and creativity; and they are found outside of the standard high school curriculum.</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Finding student collaborators, and working with a teacher, students prepare a formal proposal describing the project details. Schedules, finances, outcomes, and connections to learning are all integral parts of that proposal.</h3>\\r\\n', '     Flex Friday fosters the skills needed to succeed in the real world; these skills require time, responsibility, and creativity; and they are found outside of the standard high school curriculum.      Finding student collaborators, and working with a teacher, students prepare a formal proposal describing the project details. Schedules, finances, outcomes, and connections to learning are all integral parts of that proposal.');";

